<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8391150>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–4. Asindulum heads, males. 1. A. coxale, anterior. 2. A. coxale, lateral. 3. A. montanum, anterior. 4. A. montanum, lateral. Scale bars = ca. 0.5 mm. Abbreviations: asp, anterior spiracle; clyp, clypeus; cx1, coxa 1; hyphar, hypopharynx; lab, labium, lbl, labellum; lbr, labrum; mx, maxilla; plp, palpus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8391150/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8391152>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Holotype female of Asindulum coxale and labels. Clockwise spiral from top: Wing, scale bar = 1.0 mm. Head (anterior), scale bar = 1.0 mm. Habitus (anteroventral), scale bar = 2.0 mm. Habitus (posterodorsal), scale bar = 2.0 mm. Habitus (lateral), scale bar = 2.0 mm. Type labels. Photos by Charles Whittemore Farnum, credited to, and used with permission by, Museum of Comparative Zoology, Harvard University. Abbreviations: cx1, coxa 1; lbl, labellum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8391152/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8391158>
    dc:description "FIGURES 13–15. Asindulum coxale, female terminalia.13. Ventral. 14. Dorsal. 15. Lateral. Scale = ca. 0.25 mm.Abbreviations: ce, cercus; s7, sternite 7; s8, sternite 8; s10, sternite 10; t7, tergite 7." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8391158/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8391217>
    dc:description "FIGURE 85. Distribution map for Asindulum coxale, Asindulum flavidum n. sp., and Asindulum mexicanum n. sp.." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8391217/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8408453>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Asindulum coxale, male habitus. Scale = ca. 1.0 mm." ;
